author: Billy S.C Ticoalu
classification: Austronesian, Malayo-Polynesian, Philippine, Minahasan, North, Northeast

author: to sniff, smell
glottocode: to breathe air in through your nose in a way that makes a sound, especially when you are crying, have a cold, etc

author: to split
glottocode: separate or cut with a tool, such as a sharp instrument

author: to grow
glottocode: to grow but has a broader meaning

author: louse
glottocode: general term - probably an Indonesian loan
